1. Grant of Rights
The UHS-OSA Open Core is provided free of charge for use, implementation, adaptation and application in any organization, system or product.
No prior approval or agreement is required for use of the Open Core.
2. Scope of Open Core
The Open Core includes:
- Operational Decimal Classification (ODC) levels 1–4 and levels 4-6 for class 011 OMA Operation Manual
- structural models and perspective logic
- principles for portals, folders and navigation
3. Attribution (Mandatory)
All implementations shall include the following attribution:
“Based on the Universal Holistic System (UHS) by Sven von Zweigbergk.”
The attribution shall be visible in documentation, user interfaces or metadata where applicable.
4. Separation of Materials
Materials beyond the Open Core, including but not limited to:
- detailed classification structures
- templates and reference implementations
- governance, certification and ecosystem services
are not part of this license and may be subject to separate agreements.
